[ f(x)=3 ] Una definicion Definition (l.e.s): A long sequence of objects (in our case usually groups or pointed spaces) $$ \cdots \longrightarrow A_{n+1} \overset{d_{n+1}} \longrightarrow A_n \overset{d_n} \longrightarrow A_{n-1} \longrightarrow \cdots $$ is called exact at $A_n$ if $\text{Ker}(d_n)=\text{Im}(d_{n+1})$ . The sequence is called exact if it is exact for every $n.$ Seccion 1 Algun texto Seccion 2 mas texto $$\cdots \rightarrow [\Sigma^n S^0, X] \rightarrow [\Sigma^n S^0, Y] \rightarrow [\Sigma^{n-1} S^0, hofib(p)] \rightarrow \cdots .
